  "texts": [
    "In this description, Theorem 3.5 can be recast asA(Σ) ≃ Z(C)(1 → Tr χ ⊗S 1 ⊗ • • • ⊗ Tr χ ⊗Sm).",
    "(18)For later use, we investigate how the map Φ Σ changes when we modify the anchor using Dehn twists around the holes of Σ. Lemma 3.7.",
    "Let Σ be a decorated surface homeomorphic to the sphere with m holes cut out.",
    "Let and ′ be anchors for Σ so that ′ is obtained from by a Dehn twist around boundary component S κ. ThenΦ ′ Σ α ⊗ w 1 ⊗ • • • ⊗ w m = θ Xκ × Φ Σ α ⊗ w 1 ⊗ • • • ⊗ w m (19)for any α ∈ Z(C)(1 → X 1 ⊗ • • • ⊗ X m) and any w κ ∈ C(X κ → χ ⊗S κ) for κ = 1, • • •, m. Here θ Xκ ∈ U (1) is the twist of X κ ∈ Irr Z(C), defined for any X ∈ Ob Z(C) by = θ X ×.",
    "(20)Proof:Writing K = ( m κ=1 d Xκ) 1/2 D m-1 we find Φ ′ Σ α ⊗ w 1 ⊗ • • • ⊗ w m = K × = K × = K × θ Xκ × = θ Xκ × Φ Σ α ⊗ w 1 ⊗ • • • ⊗ w m,where we used the cloaking property of the dotted line in the second step."
  ]
}